  <bioghist id="aspace_092cbfa9b0de13790137c3161c4f0e37">
    <head>Biography</head>
<p>In 1961, Dean Francis Cheever hired Dr. Ernst Knobil to lead the newly established Physiology Department, which was to be separated from the Pharmacology Department. Dr. Knobil left Harvard to become the first Richard Beatty Mellon endowed chair of physiology at the University of Pittsburgh. He developed the department from scratch using a grant of more than one million dollars from the R.K. Mellon Foundation and focused the department's research on his area of study, endocrine physiology, to distinguish it from other programs over the course of twenty years. Dr. Knobil left the University of Pittsburgh in 1981 to become Dean of the University of Texas Medical School in Houston.</p>  </bioghist>
